parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the airbag inflator recall can lead to a risk of injury or death to vehicle occupants, as the inflator may rupture and cause metal fragments to pass through the airbag and into the vehicle interior.
symptoms: None reported
as the issue is related to a recall repair delay rather than a specific failure or symptom.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blind spot detection system can lead to accidents, especially when changing lanes or backing up, as the driver may not be aware of vehicles or pedestrians in the blind spot.
symptoms: The blind spot detection system warning light appears on the dashboard
the system fails to detect vehicles or pedestrians in the blind spot
the system malfunctions or stops working altogether.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety issues, including loss of power, faulty brakes, and malfunctioning safety features, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The power windows or doors do not work
the brake pedal squeaks
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the air conditioning blows warm air
the fuel gauge misreads
the horn stops working.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of safety features, such as traction control, stability control, and airbag systems, can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The traction control or stability control warning lights appear on the dashboard
the vehicle loses power or stalls
the airbag warning light appears on the dashboard
the seatbelt warning system does not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult or impossible to turn, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes hard to turn
the steering wheel is stiff
the steering wheel makes a whining or squeaking noise
the power steering fluid level is low
the vehicle is difficult to maneuver
especially at low speeds.
